What do you have to
say for yourself?

15:25.625 --> 15:27.292
Okay, then I'll start.

15:27.294 --> 15:29.761
That was wrong, Phil.
You could have really hurt him.

15:29.763 --> 15:32.397
Yeah, you can't do that, man.
He was just standing there.

15:32.399 --> 15:34.399
Yeah, we all know
Tandy's a tool,

15:34.401 --> 15:37.368
but you can't just punch up
on someone's face for that.

15:37.370 --> 15:39.904
Yeah, being a tool is annoying,
but it's not a crime.

15:39.906 --> 15:41.906
Okay, thank you
for the support, guys.

15:41.908 --> 15:44.142
I, uh, disagree
with the tool stuff, but, uh,

15:44.144 --> 15:46.077
you know, appreciate
the... the sentiment.

15:46.079 --> 15:47.912
But, look, I provoked him, okay?

15:47.914 --> 15:50.648
I-I didn't mean to,
but I did it, okay?

15:50.650 --> 15:52.216
You shouldn't have punched me,

15:52.218 --> 15:53.885
but, you know,
let's just

15:53.887 --> 15:55.887
move on from this, okay?
GAIL: No!

15:55.889 --> 15:57.088
You need to
be punished!

15:57.090 --> 15:58.423
You do the crime,
you do the time.

15:58.425 --> 15:59.824
Do you remember that, Phil?

15:59.826 --> 16:02.226
I think we ought to make him
touch that wire.

16:02.228 --> 16:03.761
No, we have a system
of punishment

16:03.763 --> 16:04.963
that works-- the stocks!

16:04.965 --> 16:07.131
Tandy did it, I did it,
and it works!

16:07.133 --> 16:08.733
Now it's Phil's turn!

16:08.735 --> 16:09.734
CAROL:
Well, how many days

16:09.736 --> 16:11.169
for a person
punching someone?

16:11.171 --> 16:12.670
We got a day for bacon.

16:12.672 --> 16:14.172
This is much worse than bacon.

16:14.174 --> 16:15.907
This is assault.

16:15.909 --> 16:17.075
So, what, two days?

16:17.077 --> 16:18.309
That sounds good.

16:18.311 --> 16:19.944
Yeah, all right,
so two days it is.

16:19.946 --> 16:21.512
Off to the stocks, Phil.

16:21.514 --> 16:23.414
No.

16:23.416 --> 16:25.016
Yeah-huh.

16:25.018 --> 16:26.751
Nope.
